The Greek government said it sold
four Airbus A340-300 aircraft that were previously leased by
former state-run  Olympic Airlines SA (OLYA) .  Apollo Aviation Group was the highest bidder for the
airplanes, according to a  statement  posted on the Ministry of
Financeâ€™s website on Dec. 30. No financial details on the
aircraft sale were given.  The decision was made Dec. 23 by the Inter-ministerial
Committee on Privatization and Restructuring, according to the
